Interface SnippetOutcome

All Known Subinterfaces:
SnippetOutcome.CompilerError, SnippetOutcome.ControlViolation, SnippetOutcome.ExceptionThrown, SnippetOutcome.Interrupted, SnippetOutcome.Overwritten, SnippetOutcome.Skipped, SnippetOutcome.Successful, SnippetOutcome.SuccessfulNoValue, SnippetOutcome.SuccessfulWithValue, SnippetOutcome.Suspended, SnippetOutcome.UnresolvedReferences
public sealed interface SnippetOutcome permits SnippetOutcome.CompilerError, SnippetOutcome.ControlViolation, SnippetOutcome.UnresolvedReferences, SnippetOutcome.Overwritten, SnippetOutcome.Suspended, SnippetOutcome.Interrupted, SnippetOutcome.Skipped, SnippetOutcome.ExceptionThrown, SnippetOutcome.Successful (not exhaustive)
Captures the outcome from one of the Snippets that constitute a JavaBox script.

A snippet can fail by failing to compile, compiling into bytecode that violates a Control, throwing an exception during execution, etc.

    Interface
    Description
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.CompilerError
    Indicates failure due to one or more compiler errors.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.ControlViolation
    Indicates that the bytecode generated by the snippet could not be loaded because it violated some Control.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.ExceptionThrown
    Indicates an exception was thrown during the execution of the snippet.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.HaltsScript
    Implemented by SnippetOutcomes that will cause a script to stop executing.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.HasException<T extends Throwable>
    Implemented by SnippetOutcomes for which there is an associated exception.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.Interrupted
    Indicates that the snippet's execution was interrupted.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.Overwritten
    Indicates that a declaration was successfully compiled, but the declaration was overwritten by a later snippet in the same source.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.Skipped
    Indicates that the snippet's was not executed (yet).
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.Successful
    Indicates a successful outcome.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.SuccessfulNoValue
    Indicates a successful outcome for which no value was returned, e.g., the invocation of a void method, a declaration for which no unresolved references remain, etc.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.SuccessfulWithValue
    Indicates a successful outcome for which some value was returned, e.g., an evaluated expression or the invocation of a non-void method.
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.Suspended
    Indicates that the snippet invoked JavaBox.suspend().
    static interface 
    SnippetOutcome.UnresolvedReferences
    Indicates that a declaration was successful but it contained unresolved references and those references were not resolved by any subsequent snippets in the same source.
